{"type":"message","id":"59825cd0","parentId":"e2a5cad7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:15:38.418Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wpqvjn2z2sgl_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 3805\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1671\n[mutation proposed] research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 33d3b13] pulse: 2026-03-24 131516\n 5 files changed, 237 insertions(+), 98 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131516.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 131516.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131516 - The CFI compression synthesis revealed the constant-format problem (tokens with freq�160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not causal signals). The next concrete step is implementing Strategy C: the hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 scoring experiment.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"kind-river","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 3805\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1671\n[mutation proposed] research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md\n[master 33d3b13] pulse: 2026-03-24 131516\n 5 files changed, 237 insertions(+), 98 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 131516.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 131516.mutation\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 131516 - The CFI compression synthesis revealed the constant-format problem (tokens with freq�160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts, not causal signals). The next concrete step is implementing Strategy C: the hybrid CFIxFreq^0.5 scoring experiment.\n","name":"powershell C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372538416}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef874f1b","parentId":"59825cd0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:15:38.422Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_wpqvjn2z2sgl_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 131415\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/CFI_STRATEGY_C_HYBRID.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals and recent findings:\r\n\r\n1. **CFI Compression Experiment completed** - Found that CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n2. **Key insight about constant format tokens** - Tokens like \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\" have freq=160, CFI=1.00 - they're metaprogramming artifacts, not actual information\r\n3. **Three-dimensional filter identified**: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n4. **Next step**: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n\r\nThe next logical action from the synthesis document is to run the hybrid scoring experiment. The proposed scoring function is:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThis would:\r\n1. Filter out constant format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1.00 → score would be 1.0 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0, still problematic)\r\n2. Actually need to adjust for this...\r\n\r\nWait, let me re-read. The constant format tokens have:\r\n- freq=160, CFI=1.00\r\n- score = 1.00 × min(1, 160/120) = 1.00 × 1.0 = 1.0\r\n\r\nThat's still too high! The insight says \"CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\" which means freq must be < 120. So for freq=160, even with CFI=1.00, it gets filtered out because freq ≥ 120.\r\n\r\nSo the filter should be:\r\n- CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n\r\n\r\n- This captures meaningful tokens like \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96) and \"completed at:\" (freq=160, CFI=1.00) differently\r\n- I'll need to run an experiment to validate the scoring function's effectiveness in distinguishing informative patterns\r\n\r\nI'll design a systematic test to compare the hybrid scoring approach against previous filtering methods, tracking precision and recall carefully.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that three-dimensional filtering (CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)) correctly handles constant-format tokens, but the proposed hybrid scoring formula (CFI × min(1, freq/120)) needs validation to ensure it properly weights informative vs. metaprogramming tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nRun the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) to test the composite scoring formula against binary threshold approaches, comparing precision/recall on the same 200-pulse dataset.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 Scoring Experiment\r\n*Started: 2026-03-24 1315*\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nA continuous scoring function combining both signals will outperform binary thresholds:\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis formula:\r\n- Penalizes constant-format tokens (freq=160 → capped at 1.0, but freq ≥ 120 triggers filter)\r\n- Rewards research trajectory tokens (freq~100, CFI~0.9 → score ~0.75)\r\n- Normalizes both dimensions into single comparable metric\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Test Configurations\r\n| Config | Score Threshold | Additional Filters | Expected Behavior |\r\n|--------|-----------------|-------------------|-------------------|\r\n| C1 | score ≥ 0.5 | freq < 120 | Baseline hybrid |\r\n| C2 | score ≥ 0.6 | freq < 120 | Stricter scoring |\r\n| C3 | score ≥ 0.5 | freq ∈ [3, 120) | + Minimum frequency |\r\n| C4 | score ≥ 0.4 | freq ∈ [3, 120) | Lenient scoring |\r\n\r\n### Token Classification\r\n- **Informative**: freq ∈ [3, 120), CFI ≥ 0.5, score ≥ threshold\r\n- **Metaprogramming**: freq ≥ 120 OR CFI ≥ 0.95 (constant format)\r\n- **Noise**: freq < 3 OR score < threshold\r\n\r\n## Analysis Script\r\n\r\n```python\r\n# TODO: Implement scoring experiment\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Results\r\n\r\n### Configuration C1: score ≥ 0.5, freq < 120\r\n*Pending run*\r\n\r\n### Configuration C2: score ≥ 0.6, freq < 120\r\n*Pending run*\r\n\r\n### Configuration C3: score ≥ 0.5, freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n*Pending run*\r\n\r\n### Configuration C4: score ≥ 0.4, freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n*Pending run*\r\n\r\n## Key Test Cases\r\n\r\n| Token | freq | CFI | Expected Score | Expected Class |\r\n|-------|------|-----|----------------|----------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | Filtered (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"completed at:\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | Filtered (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | 1.00 | Filtered (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96 | Filtered (freq≥120) |\r\n| \"research\" | 98 | 0.85 | 0.70 | INCLUDED (C3/C4) |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 64 | 0.\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:14:37\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372538418}}
