{"type":"message","id":"410ad27e","parentId":"9c4d2407","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:15:50.500Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse completed successfully. Let me summarize what happened:\n\n1. The pulse ran the CFI Compression Synthesis which identified the constant-format problem\n2. It created a new experiment file: `research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md`\n3. It committed changes with the message \"pulse: 2026-03-24 131516\"\n4. Created a mutation proposal file: `mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 131516.mutation`\n\nKey findings:\n- Tokens like \"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\" have freq=160, CFI=1.00 — they're metaprogramming artifacts\n\n\n- The real challenge is filtering out these constant-format tokens while keeping actual research signals intact, which requires balancing CFI ≥ 0.5 with freq thresholds in the [3, 120) range\n\nThe next phase involves testing a composite scoring formula that multiplies CFI by a normalized frequency component to better discriminate between meaningful patterns and these artifact tokens.","thinkingSignature":"35e0d2bbc3849cf4708f448d31392530880b7a7d0c820d883b694ee96f657fe9"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse — 2026-03-24 13:15:16 ✅**\n\n**What happened:**\n- Completed CFI Compression Synthesis (`research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`)\n- Identified a critical flaw: constant-format tokens (\"for next instantiation\", \"pulse\", \"completed at:\") all have **freq=160, CFI=1.00** — they're metaprogramming artifacts, not causal research signals\n- Binary CFI threshold alone can't distinguish them from meaningful tokens like \"Phase 1\" (freq=136, CFI=0.96)\n\n**Key insight unlocked:**\nThree-dimensional filter needed: **CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)** — this filters out the constant-format tokens at freq=160 while capturing mid-frequency informative tokens.\n\n**Mutation applied:** `research/HYBRID_CFI_FREQ_EXPERIMENT.md` — proposes Strategy C: a composite scoring formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` to test against binary threshold approaches.\n\n**Committed:** `master 33d3b13` — 5 files changed, +237 insertions, -98 deletions.\n\n**Next step waiting:** Implement and run the hybrid scoring experiment to validate which scoring approach best separates research signal from metaprogramming noise."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2090,"output":492,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14719,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372542031}}
